alternatives.name: RELEASE

alternatives.nonste_example: Let the fuel vent freely overboard.

alternatives.name: AIRFLOW
alternatives.ste_example: MAKE SURE THAT THE AREA WHERE YOU WILL USE THIS SOLVENT HAS GOOD AIRFLOW.
alternatives.nonste_example: Ventilate the area where this solvent is used.

alternatives.name: AIRFLOW
alternatives.ste_example: MAKE SURE THAT THE AIRFLOW IS SUFFICIENT.
alternatives.nonste_example: Make sure that the ventilation is sufficient.

alternatives.nonste_example: Get access via No. 6 break-in panel.

meanings.ste_example: PRESSURE SURGES AND VIBRATION CAN CAUSE WEAR ON THE HOSES.

alternatives.name: NEAR
alternatives.ste_example: MAKE SURE THAT SOLVENTS ARE NOT NEAR THE ENGINE EXHAUST.

alternatives.name: ADJACENT

alternatives.name: FORCE

alternatives.nonste_example: Vigorous cleaning with a brush can cause damage to the carpet.

alternatives.name: FORCE

alternatives.nonste_example: Do not move the control wheel too vigorously.

alternatives.name: SEE

meanings.value: The sound you make when you speak
meanings.ste_example: SPEAK INTO THE MICROPHONE IN YOUR USUAL VOICE.

note.value: Use a different construction. Tell the reader what the risk or effect is.

meanings.value: 1. The space that an object fills

TO ADJUST THE VOLUME, USE THE BUTTONS ON THE SIDE OF THE PHONE.

meanings.value: To stop doing something while another thing occurs.
meanings.ste_example: (1) IF THE STATUS OF THE FAULT IS “NOT CONFIRMED”: (a) OPEN THE APPLICABLE CIRCUITBREAKER. (b) WAIT FOR 4 MINUTES. (c) DO THE BITE TEST.

meanings.value: To move on foot from one location to a different location
meanings.ste_example: DO NOT WALK ON THIS AREA.

KEEP THE GASKETS IN A WARM, DRY AREA.

alternatives.nonste_example: Warm the mixture before use.

alternatives.nonste_example: Warn personnel to stay away from the conveyor system.

alternatives.name: CLEAN

alternatives.nonste_example: Watch for air bubbles.

note.value: Do not use this pronoun for other meanings.

words.name: PUT ON

words.nonste_example: Wear protective clothing when you use the solvent.

meanings.value: Conditions of the atmosphere: temperature, moisture, winds, and clouds

meanings.value: The force caused when gravity acts on the mass of an object

meanings.value: That has liquid on it, in it, or absorbed into it

meanings.value: At, to, or in which location

alternatives.nonste_example: The whole procedure must be done.

alternatives.name: ALL

alternatives.nonste_example: The system is wholly automatic.

note.value: Use a different construction.

meanings.value: That has a specified or large width

meanings.value: The smaller of two dimensions, the second-largest of three dimensions

meanings.value: Auxiliary modal verb that shows simple future tense

note.value: No other verb forms.

meanings.value: To move around and around an object

meanings.ste_example: SMALL DAMAGE IS PERMITTED WITHOUT REPAIR. REFER TO TABLE 1 FOR THE APPLICABLE LIMITS.

meanings.value: To record data or information as words, letters, or symbols

meanings.ste_example: DO NOT REMOVE THE FIXTURE COVER AT THIS TIME.
meanings.nonste_example: Do not remove the fixture cover yet.

meanings.ste_example: YOU CAN CONTINUE THE TEST.

meanings.value: Related to the reader or the user

alternatives.name: YOU
alternatives.ste_example: DO NOT USE YOUR HANDS TO PREVENT MOVEMENT OF THE LP COMPRESSOR. IF YOU DO, THE LP COMPRESSOR CAN CAUSE YOU INJURY AND CAN CAUSE DAMAGE TO THE EQUIPMENT.
alternatives.nonste_example: Do not use your hands to prevent movement of the LP compressor. If you do, you can cause injury to yourself and damage to the equipment.
